message.content:
A bighorn is a species of wild sheep that inhabits western North America.
They are typically light brown with white underbelly and have a distinctive pair of large, curved horns on their head.
These horns can weigh up to 30 pounds and can reach lengths of up to 3 feet.
The horns are used for territorial battles between males and as a means of defense against predators.
Bighorns have excellent climbing skills and can often be found scaling steep rocky terrain in mountains.
They are herbivorous animals and primarily graze on grasses and shrubs.
In the wild, bighorns typically form small herds and are often seen roaming around in search of food and water.
